Hello!
Are you an experienced Fullstack Developer (from mid level upwards) looking to grow,later this year (not ASAP), in a team of highly-skilled, top-talent innovators while working on multiple products in a range of industries?
If so, Altar may be the right place for you -later this year.We are not in need of someone to join us immediately in this role, but we are interested in getting to know great candidates that would beinterested in joining us later in the year.If you are looking to move to a new role right now, maybe Altar isn't the best option. If you are not in a rush but want to secure agreat new job later this year,please keep on reading this job description and apply if it makes sense to you!

With us, you’ll help entrepreneurs and business leaders build innovative products that transform their industries, from early-stage MVPs to disruptive satellite products.
You’ll have the opportunity to work with a host of entrepreneurs and business leaders, like an ex-Product Owner of YouTube and a former Managing Director of HSBC. Not to mention, exciting companies like the multi-award-winning regtech startup, Apiax or Coca–Cola.
As aSeniorFullstack Developer, you will be working with both the front and back ends of websites/applications. You will provide a complete, end-to-end service for demanding web projects.
With us, you’ll not be alone working in these cutting-edge technologies. You’ll be among a cross-functional team of seasoned Altarions with expertise in a multitude of sectors, from fintech and marketplace to AI and IoT.
What You’ll Be Doing:
As a Senior Fullstack Developer, you’ll be:
- Able to collaborate on any phase of the development flow, namely, Database queries, Back-End, Front-End, and DevOps;
- Responsible for writing Unit and Integration Tests for BE and FE Code;
- Requirement gathering and project planning rituals.
The Hands-On Experience We Need You to Bring to the Table:
- 6+ years of experience with Web Application Development;
- Professional experience in working with JavaScript frameworks, such as Angular, React.js or Vue.js;
- Experience with traditional Databases, namely MongoDB and PostgreSQL;
- Experience writing “single-threaded” Node.js applications;
- Some experience with modern CSS Frameworks such as TailwindsCSS;
- Fluency in both written and spoken English.
The Extra Experience We’d Love to See:
- Experience with writing Python or GO applications;
- Experience working with major cloud vendors such as GCP and AWS.

Check our cutting-edge tech stack here

Our recruitment process:
- CV screening (ASAP)
- Recruiter interview (60 min)
- Tech Challenge (from home, 5-day deadline)
- Tech Interview w/ our CTO (60 min)
- Final interview w/ our CEO (~60min)
We will go through the process as quickly as possible and we'll keep you up-to-date along the way. If we come to a point in which everything is aligned and it becomes clear to us and to you that we should be working together, we'll share with you the good news and we'll wait for the right time, later in the year, to extend you an offer.

What you can expect from working with us:
Full focus on helping you make the most out of life
